SUMMARY:Free Tax Help
DTSTAMP:20260327T061036Z
DTSTART:20260327T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Friday\, March 27\, 2026\, 11am - 4pm\n\nTrained volunteers wil
	l be available to answer questions and prepare personal tax returns.\n\nLo
	cation Link:\n\nSouthwest Branch\n\nRoom Location: Meeting Room\n\nRegistr
	ation Required: Registration is not required.\n\nDetailed Description: Thi
	s service is free and available to individuals only. The free service is n
	ot available for business tax returns. To receive tax help\, bring the fol
	lowing documents:\,\n\nRequired:\n\nPhoto identification\, Social Security
	 cards or Individual Taxpayer Identification Numbers \\(ITIN\\) for everyo
	ne listed on the tax return.\, Proof of income\, for example\, W2s and 109
	9s \\(Social Security benefits\\)\, Official documents on Social Security 
	Administration letterhead\, Medicare card \\(if Social Security number is 
	followed by an "A"\\)\, Be prepared to provide information about health ca
	re coverage for each person on the return.\,\n\nRecommended:\n\nLast year&
	's tax return\, if available\, Bank account and routing numbers for direct
	 deposit of refunds\, Photocopies or computer print-outs of any of these d
	ocuments willbe accepted.\, Due to federal budget cuts the IRS is unable t
	o provide the Library with certain tax forms and instruction booklets.\, M
	ost IRS forms are available online at\n\nwww.irs.gov .\, You may make free
	 black-and-white prints of the forms from Library computers:\n\nwww.spl.or
	g/Print \, Thanks to our partner\n\nAARP .\n\nEvent Logistics: Appointment
	s are not required but recommended. Register\n\nhere. \, AARP Tax Help loc
	ations serve anyone who earned less than $80\,000 in 2025.\, For eligibili
	ty details\, contact AARP at 888-227-7669.\,\n\nContact Us: If you have qu
	estions about this event\,\n\nAsk Us\n\nor call 206-386-4636.\n\nADA Accom
	modations: We can provide accommodations for people with disabilities at L
	ibrary events. Please\n\ncontactLEAP\n\nat least seven days before the eve
	nt to request accommodations.\, All Library programs are free and open to 
	the public.\, The Southwest Branch is accessible by the 21\, 22\, and C Li
	ne buses.\, Free parking in our lot and free street parking is available.\
	, The second-floor meeting room is accessible by elevator\, or two flights
	 of stairs with railings. ADA-accessible restrooms are available on the se
	cond floor.\, Ask staff if you need assistive devices \\(such as magnifyin
	g glasses\\) during the event.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/de
	tails/free-tax-help/18162991/2026-03-27T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Cultu
	re
